Important Information for CAT 2019 Exam Preparation

CAT 2019 Important Dates

CAT 2019 Online Registration Starts: August First Week

CAT 2019 Online Registration Ends: Mid September

CAT 2019 Admit Card Release: Mid October

CAT 2019 Exam Date: Last Sunday of November/First Sunday of December

CAT 2019 Result Date: Second Week of January

  • CAT 2019 Exam: Important Dates & Eligibility
CAT 2019 Exam Pattern & Syllabus

Time: 3 hours

Total No. of questions: 100

Verbal Ability & Reading Comprehension: 34

Logical Reasoning & Data Interpretation: 32

Quantitative Aptitude: 34

  • CAT Exam Pattern & Syllabus
CAT 2019 Preparation Books

Here are the books recommended by CAT 2018 toppers which every CAT 2019 aspirant should refer to. The list consists of the Physical books and Online resources from which any CAT 2019 aspirant can improve their scores in CAT VARC, LRDI and Quant Section.

  • CAT 2019 Preparation Books and Online Resources
CAT Preparation in 6 Months

Thinking of preparing in the last 6 months? Here is how to prepare for CAT 2019 in 6 months and how CAT 2019 Online Preparation will be helpful to get a good score in the CAT 2019 Exam.

  • 6 Month CAT Preparation Strategy
CAT Preparation Strategy for Working Professionals

With a majority of working professionals facing issues of time management and balancing work with CAT 2019 Preparation, we bring to you CAT 2019 Study Plan and strategy for Working Professionals.

  • CAT 2019 Preparation Strategy for Working Professionals
CAT 2019 Preparation Strategy for College Students

Most of the college-going students struggle with the question: What is an effective time table for CAT preparation for a college student?
We bring you the complete strategy for a college student to crack CAT.

  • CAT 2019 Preparation Strategy for College Students
Should I take a drop to prepare for CAT exam?

‘Should I take a drop to prepare for CAT’? is a common question among MBA aspirants and one can easily observe them having queries about it on different social forums. While we understand the apprehension is right on your part, let us delve deep into the issue and see how should we arrive at an informed decision when it comes to this dilemma

  • How to Justify drop for CAT exam?
